      <abstract label="Abstract">This collection consists of the
         business papers of the Albemarle Soapstone Company, Alberene,
         Virginia, described as manufacturers of Alberene Stone Laundry
         Tubs &amp; Sinks, and including some of its associate
         businesses, the Nelson and Albemarle Railway Company and the
         Virginia Soapstone Company, Schuyler, Virginia, 1885-1907 and
         1919-1936. William L. Harrison was the purchasing agent for
         all three companies. Other products advertised by this company
         include: sinks, acid tanks, foot warmers, griddles,
         fireplaces, and register borders.</abstract>
    </did>
